## Specs-P2 Goals View Refinement — Tree UX, Modal Editor, and Tag System
**Status:** done
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** Specs-G7, Specs-P1

| Task | Owner | Duration | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| Specs-P25.1 | Replace table-based GoalsTable with div-based tree nodes | UI | 1 day | Done |
| Specs-P25.2 | Implement toggle area: fixed 2.5rem, count+chevron combined, removed for leaf goals | UI | 0.5 day | Done |
| Specs-P25.3 | GoalDetailModal: centered modal with header/meta/body/footer, inline edit | UI | 1 day | Done |
| Specs-P25.4 | Tag all 52 goals and 6 other categories with `stack:*` and `module:*` | Docs | 0.5 day | Done |
| Specs-P25.5 | Tag display: shortened values, color-coded badges (stack=blue, module=purple) | UI | 0.5 day | Done |
| Specs-P25.6 | Module accordion sidebar: Overview entry + per-module Outline + type navigation, Stack filter retained | UI | 1 day | Done |
| Specs-P25.7 | Backend flat mode fix: `get_or_default` falls back to flat doc on key miss | Backend | 0.5 day | Done |

- **Outcome**: Goals section now shows a clean hierarchical tree with expandable sub-goals, modal-based detail editing, and sidebar tag filtering.
- **Risk**: None — incremental UX polish on existing Specs-P1 foundation.
